# Running the CodeRabbit CLI

CodeRabbit is available in the terminal—use it to review code before or alongside human review.

- **Help:** `cr -h` (alias: `coderabbit -h`) — use either `cr` or `coderabbit` interchangeably for available commands.
- **Default:** Prefer the **`--agent`** flag so output fits agent workflows.

## Uncommitted changes (most common)

```bash
coderabbit --agent -t uncommitted
```

Use this to review what’s staged/uncommitted in the working tree.

## Limit

**Do not run CodeRabbit more than 3 times for a single coherent set of changes** (same branch / same PR-sized edit). If follow-up edits are substantial, treat as a new set and stay within the limit again.

Reason: to avoid review fatigue and maintain efficiency.
